        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-10-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-10-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="731" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d731">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.01/10–245</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The British Prime Minister</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Attlee</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to President <persName type="to">Truman</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="51" xml:id="d731fn51">Copy transmitted to the Acting Secretary of State
                        by the British Ambassador in a letter of October 2, 1945, not
                        printed.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-10-01">October 1,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>14. In view of statements in Washington that I did not send a reply to your
                    letter to me of August 31st I feel bound to let it be known that I did in fact
                    send a reply on September 16th and that I understood no further action would be
                    taken until after Mr. Byrnes had returned to Washington. I think you will agree
                    that otherwise a very false impression might be created.</p>
                <p>The question of immigration referred to in last sentence of my telegram to you
                    No. 9 of September 16th is still under consideration but I shall not fail to let
                    you know our views as soon as possible.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
